SIMPLE: temporize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Temporize
<hw>Tem"po*rize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Temporized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Temporizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>temporiser</ets>. See <er>Temporal</er> of time.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To comply with the time or occasion; to humor, or yield to, the
current of opinion or circumstances; also, to trim, as between two
parties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They might their grievance inwardly complain,⟦br⟧
But outwardly they needs must <qex>temporize</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To delay; to procrastinate.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To comply; to agree.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Temporizer</ent>⟦br⟧
